Pep Guardiola says he was ‘upset’ that he wasn’t invited by his players after a video of Jack Grealish emerged. Grealish, Riyad Mahrez, and Kyle Walker were all captured on video outside Albert’s Schloss, in Manchester, on Sunday. No club curfews were broken, and it happened a day after Manchester City’s 4-1 FA Cup win over Fulham. Qatar 2022 Race: NFF Confirms Venue, Date For Nigeria, Ghana… Guardiola Provides Major Injury Update Ahead Of PL Clash With… And Guardiola has joked he was ‘upset’ he wasn’t invited by the players when asked about the video in his pre-match press conference. The City boss then quipped he was going to fine the players because of the ‘snub. “And I don’t like it, next time hopefully they will invite me.” The Catalan boss then added: “The video didn’t show what happened. They had dinner together, and they were sober.